description: Latin germinātus, past participle of germināre (“to sprout”).

verbs.description: germinate (third-person singular simple present germinates, present participle germinating, simple past and past participle germinated)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, botany, horticulture) Of a seed, to begin to grow, to sprout roots and leaves.
(transitive) To cause to grow; to produce.
